				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I read that if PPU rendering was off, the palette address chosen by $2006 would determine the color to be rendered on screen, and the color could be changed on screen by $2007.  Would it be possible to do something similar, with PPU rendering and $2006 set to a palette address, and have hardware inside a cartridge changing the PPU data bus?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

